The lack of security at the country's largest museum has since been called into question and the brutality has led to large scale solidarity protests in Tunis, both at the weekend and in the immediate aftermath of the attack. 

Several people were arrested by Tunisian security forces after the attacks.  

The government now plans to deploy the army to major cities to bolster security following the shootings

On Saturday French President Francois Hollande confirmed Huguette Dupeu had died from her injuries following the attack.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

